# .bigbrainignore — what to keep out of `bigbrain:bootstrap` scans.
# Same syntax as .gitignore. Place this file at your repo root.
#
# Defaults already exclude:
#   - Build / cache dirs: node_modules/, dist/, build/, .venv/, __pycache__,
#     .next/, .nuxt/, .cache/, .pytest_cache/, .mypy_cache/, .ruff_cache/,
#     coverage/, htmlcov/
#   - Meta-scaffolding: .claude/, .github/, .gitlab/, .vscode/, .idea/,
#     .zed/, .agents/
#   - Our own outputs: graphify-out/, .bigbrain/
#   - Common AI-tool configs at root: .impeccable.md, .cursor.md,
#     .cursorrules, .aider.conf.yml, .aiderrc.md, .copilot.md, .windsurf.md
#   - Low-signal: CHANGELOG.md, LICENSE.md
#
# Use this file to:
#   1. Add repo-specific noise (legacy docs, vendored READMEs, etc.)
#   2. Re-include something a default excludes (negate with `!pattern`)
#
# Precedence, lowest → highest:
#   defaults  <  .ignore  <  .bigbrainignore
#
# So a `!pattern` here overrides both defaults and `.ignore`.

# --- Examples (remove / replace with your own) ---

# Drop an entire stale docs subtree
# docs/legacy/

# Drop a single one-off file
# RUNBOOK-old.md

# Re-include a default-excluded file (e.g. you actually do want
# .github/CONTRIBUTING.md in the bootstrap)
# !.github/CONTRIBUTING.md
